## Reconciliation: "Git Wins"

When git pull brings JSONL changes that conflict with CRDT state:

```typescript
class SudocodeMeshService {
  async onGitPull() {
    // 1. Pause CRDT sync
    this.provider.pause()

    // 2. Load JSONL as source of truth
    const jsonlSpecs = await this.loadJSONL('specs.jsonl')
    const jsonlIssues = await this.loadJSONL('issues.jsonl')

    // 3. Rebuild CRDT from JSONL
    const specs = this.provider.getMap('specs')
    specs.clear()
    for (const spec of jsonlSpecs) {
      specs.set(spec.id, specToYjs(spec))
    }

    // 4. Resume sync (broadcasts rebuilt state)
    this.provider.resume()

    // 5. Rebuild SQLite cache
    await this.rebuildCache()
  }
}
```

### Conflict Scenarios

| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Remote CRDT update while offline | Apply on reconnect, then persist to JSONL |
| Git pull with conflicts | JSONL wins, rebuild CRDT |
| Simultaneous edit | CRDT auto-merges, persist result |
| Entity deleted in git | Remove from CRDT |
| Entity deleted in CRDT | Remove from JSONL on persist |

